Currently the NNAPI does not support c# interface for Android, and it is not distributed through nuget.
For now NNAPI support c/c++ api through Android native library, or Java api through AAR archives.
You would need to build the NNAPI library yourself, using the instruction here, https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/master/docs/execution_providers/NNAPI-ExecutionProvider.md
That clears things up, thanks! Building OnnxRuntime ourselves might be a bit too much for us right now. Is there a timeline or rough estimate on the general availability of NNAPI support for C#?
